window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Life as a tank mechanic won’t make you famous, but at least no one shoots at you.</b></p> <p>That’s what veteran maintainer Rande \"Vandal\" VanDelle of the Chevaliers Private Calvary thought. Until, during a routine maintenance patrol, he found himself fighting for his life inside the company‘s oldest upright tank.<br> <br> Bruised, battered, and barely standing, Vandal soon returns to the cockpit to bolster the ranks of a desperate defense force. As he and his fellow Chevaliers attempt to hold back the flood of turncoats, spearheaded by a legendary cadre of off-world mercenaries, Vandal must learn to master the fickle and deadly upright tanks if he wants to live to see the next contract.</p>"; 
